The African Development Bank has issued a two billion dollar five-year Global Benchmark bond due March 14, 2028. The continental bank revealed this in a statement on Thursday, describing the bond as its first of the year. The bond was issued on March 7, 2023. AfDB said that the bond is part of its funding strategy of issuing large liquid benchmark transactions. Part of the statement read, â€œThe deal enjoyed good investor demand during the first afternoon and overnight with Indications of Interest reaching USD 2.1 billion by the time books officially opened on Tuesday 7, March 2023 at 07:57 London time.